# Backend-scoped Semgrep ignore list. The repo-root .semgrepignore covers
# local dev (run from repo root); this one is what RWX's ci-backend
# materializes into the cloud workspace (the ci-backend filter doesn't
# include the repo-root file).
#
# Entries here apply to EVERY semgrep invocation. Use it only for files
# that no rule — third-party or project — should ever scan. For per-rule
# carve-outs (e.g. app/testing/ exempt from a single project rule), use
# that rule's own paths.exclude. The split between third-party rule packs
# (which broadly exclude app/testing/ via bin/ci CLI flags) and project
# rules (which scan it by default and opt-out per rule) lives in bin/ci.

# Unit test files (real code is covered by surrounding rules; assertions
# legitimately do things production rules flag).
test_*.py
**/test/test_*.py

# Migrations — autogenerated alembic output.
**/alembic/versions/
